[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":968},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F09\u002F27\u002Fday-13-put-a-helmet-on-your-express\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F09\u002F27\u002Fday-13-put-a-helmet-on-your-express\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F09\u002F27\u002Fday-13-put-a-helmet-on-your-express\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F09\u002F27\u002Fday-13-put-a-helmet-on-your-express\u002F":944,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F09\u002F27\u002Fday-13-put-a-helmet-on-your-express\u002F":953},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20230927\u002F4133508926\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":928,"date":929,"description":26,"extension":930,"lang":931,"meta":932,"navigation":571,"path":933,"readingMinutes":934,"seo":935,"standalone":936,"stem":937,"tags":938,"tldr":941,"updated":929,"url":942,"__hash__":943},"content\u002Fen\u002FNodejs\u002Fday-13-put-a-helmet-on-your-express.md","Day 13 - Put a Helmet on Your Express!","7825844140",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":915},"minimark",[11,19,24,27,31,34,37,40,43,47,55,60,67,77,80,83,89,93,96,103,106,287,290,295,324,328,331,334,345,353,357,360,367,399,402,436,440,443,482,490,494,497,516,519,642,648,661,667,809,814,852,858,877,883,898,902,905,911],[12,13,14],"p",{},[15,16],"img",{"alt":17,"src":18},"Put a Helmet on Your Express","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002Fisray_notarray_Helmet_408e4fa3-b225-4ee3-b62c-3e0df2a5bba8.png",[20,21,23],"h2",{"id":22},"intro","Intro",[12,25,26],{},"We covered CORS and Env in the previous posts — those are basic basics. Now let's introduce something special called Helmet.",[20,28,30],{"id":29},"what-is-helmet","What is Helmet?",[12,32,33],{},"Before getting into Helmet, we need to clarify something — about \"web security\".",[12,35,36],{},"Web information security is a huge topic. This post can't cover everything — web security includes things like personal account password registration rules. So this post focuses on backend security.",[12,38,39],{},"The Helmet docs explicitly mention: Helmet is middleware that helps protect your Express application. It sets various HTTP headers that help your application avoid known web attacks.",[12,41,42],{},"In short, Helmet puts a Helmet on your Express, so your app can avoid known web attacks — just like a person wearing a helmet can avoid known injuries.",[20,44,46],{"id":45},"what-does-helmet-do","What does Helmet do?",[12,48,49,50,54],{},"By default, when you use ",[51,52,53],"code",{},"app.use(helmet());",", it auto-adds things to your HTTP headers that help your app avoid known web attacks.",[56,57,59],"h3",{"id":58},"hides-the-x-powered-by-header","Hides the X-Powered-By header",[12,61,62,63,66],{},"By default, Express adds ",[51,64,65],{},"X-Powered-By: Express"," to HTTP headers. This tells attackers your app is built with Express, so they can target Express-specific attacks.",[68,69,70],"blockquote",{},[12,71,72,76],{},[73,74,75],"strong",{},"Note","\nIn real-world dev, we avoid letting attackers know what we used to build the app — when that app has a vulnerability, attackers can target the vulnerability. So basic hiding is necessary. Early in my career working with WordPress, I encountered attackers targeting WordPress vulnerabilities — so this is really important.",[12,78,79],{},"Helmet hides this header for you, so attackers can't tell your app uses Express.",[12,81,82],{},"Don't believe it? Try the Express we practiced earlier with Postman, and you'll see:",[12,84,85],{},[15,86],{"alt":87,"src":88},"X-Powered-By","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002Fx_powered-by.jpg",[56,90,92],{"id":91},"mitigates-clickjacking","Mitigates Clickjacking",[12,94,95],{},"Clickjacking is an attack where you're tricked into clicking an element on a webpage (usually a button or link). It's done by placing a transparent overlay on the page, so you think you're clicking one element but you're actually clicking another.",[12,97,98,99,102],{},"Helmet adds ",[51,100,101],{},"X-Frame-Options"," to HTTP headers, which prevents your page from being embedded in other pages and clickjacked.",[12,104,105],{},"If that's hard to picture, here's example code:",[107,108,113],"pre",{"className":109,"code":110,"language":111,"meta":112,"style":112},"language-html shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","\u003C!-- A malicious HTML form structure -->\n\u003C!DOCTYPE html>\n\u003Chtml>\n\u003Chead>\n    \u003Ctitle>Malicious page\u003C\u002Ftitle>\n\u003C\u002Fhead>\n\u003Cbody>\n    \u003Ch1>Click here to win a prize!\u003C\u002Fh1>\n    \u003Ciframe\n      src=\"hacker's site\"\n      style=\"opacity: 0; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%;\"\n      frameborder=\"0\">\n    \u003C\u002Fiframe>\n\u003C\u002Fbody>\n\u003C\u002Fhtml>\n","html","",[51,114,115,124,142,152,162,178,188,198,213,221,234,245,258,269,278],{"__ignoreMap":112},[116,117,120],"span",{"class":118,"line":119},"line",1,[116,121,123],{"class":122},"sQrFR","\u003C!-- A malicious HTML form structure -->\n",[116,125,127,131,135,139],{"class":118,"line":126},2,[116,128,130],{"class":129},"sMAXC","\u003C!",[116,132,134],{"class":133},"sKpQp","DOCTYPE",[116,136,138],{"class":137},"sCcAr"," html",[116,140,141],{"class":129},">\n",[116,143,145,148,150],{"class":118,"line":144},3,[116,146,147],{"class":129},"\u003C",[116,149,111],{"class":133},[116,151,141],{"class":129},[116,153,155,157,160],{"class":118,"line":154},4,[116,156,147],{"class":129},[116,158,159],{"class":133},"head",[116,161,141],{"class":129},[116,163,165,168,171,174,176],{"class":118,"line":164},5,[116,166,167],{"class":129},"    \u003C",[116,169,170],{"class":133},"title",[116,172,173],{"class":129},">Malicious page\u003C\u002F",[116,175,170],{"class":133},[116,177,141],{"class":129},[116,179,181,184,186],{"class":118,"line":180},6,[116,182,183],{"class":129},"\u003C\u002F",[116,185,159],{"class":133},[116,187,141],{"class":129},[116,189,191,193,196],{"class":118,"line":190},7,[116,192,147],{"class":129},[116,194,195],{"class":133},"body",[116,197,141],{"class":129},[116,199,201,203,206,209,211],{"class":118,"line":200},8,[116,202,167],{"class":129},[116,204,205],{"class":133},"h1",[116,207,208],{"class":129},">Click here to win a prize!\u003C\u002F",[116,210,205],{"class":133},[116,212,141],{"class":129},[116,214,216,218],{"class":118,"line":215},9,[116,217,167],{"class":129},[116,219,220],{"class":133},"iframe\n",[116,222,224,227,230],{"class":118,"line":223},10,[116,225,226],{"class":137},"      src",[116,228,229],{"class":129},"=",[116,231,233],{"class":232},"sTRMh","\"hacker's site\"\n",[116,235,237,240,242],{"class":118,"line":236},11,[116,238,239],{"class":137},"      style",[116,241,229],{"class":129},[116,243,244],{"class":232},"\"opacity: 0; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%;\"\n",[116,246,248,251,253,256],{"class":118,"line":247},12,[116,249,250],{"class":137},"      frameborder",[116,252,229],{"class":129},[116,254,255],{"class":232},"\"0\"",[116,257,141],{"class":129},[116,259,261,264,267],{"class":118,"line":260},13,[116,262,263],{"class":129},"    \u003C\u002F",[116,265,266],{"class":133},"iframe",[116,268,141],{"class":129},[116,270,272,274,276],{"class":118,"line":271},14,[116,273,183],{"class":129},[116,275,195],{"class":133},[116,277,141],{"class":129},[116,279,281,283,285],{"class":118,"line":280},15,[116,282,183],{"class":129},[116,284,111],{"class":133},[116,286,141],{"class":129},[12,288,289],{},"So when you click \"Click here to win a prize!\", you're actually clicking the hacker's site, not the page you wanted.",[12,291,98,292,294],{},[51,293,101],{}," to HTTP headers, preventing this when your page is embedded in another page.",[68,296,297],{},[12,298,299,301,302,305,306,305,309,312,313,315,316,323],{},[73,300,75],{},"\nThis header has three settings: ",[51,303,304],{},"DENY",", ",[51,307,308],{},"SAMEORIGIN",[51,310,311],{},"ALLOW-FROM",". The default is ",[51,314,308],{},", meaning only same-origin pages can embed it. See more ",[317,318,322],"a",{"href":319,"rel":320},"https:\u002F\u002Fdeveloper.mozilla.org\u002Fen-US\u002Fdocs\u002FWeb\u002FHTTP\u002FHeaders\u002FX-Frame-Options",[321],"nofollow","here",".",[56,325,327],{"id":326},"cross-site-request-forgery","Cross-Site Request Forgery",[12,329,330],{},"You may have seen this term — if not familiar with the Chinese name, CSRF might be more familiar. It's an attack where the attacker injects malicious things into your page. When you click, the attacker's malicious code triggers.",[12,332,333],{},"I won't go into much detail since I've written about it before:",[335,336,337],"ul",{},[338,339,340],"li",{},[317,341,344],{"href":342,"rel":343},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Fnodejs\u002F20190704\u002F2336420619\u002F",[321],"Full-Stack Warrior's Path Node.js Basics - CSRF (article in Mandarin)",[12,346,347,348,323],{},"Early defense was to add CSRF Tokens to forms. But the modern mainstream is frontend-backend separation, so we use Client Double Submit Cookie. This adds a CSRF Token to the Cookie, then puts the same CSRF Token in HTTP headers. When the backend receives the request, it compares the Cookie's CSRF Token to the HTTP header's CSRF Token — same means legit, different means illegit. Implementation reference ",[317,349,352],{"href":350,"rel":351},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Fnodejs\u002F20210527\u002F2874571028\u002F",[321],"here (article in Mandarin)",[56,354,356],{"id":355},"cross-site-scripting","Cross-Site Scripting",[12,358,359],{},"This attack is pretty common in dev — also called Cross-Site Scripting, abbreviated XSS. Most commonly seen in Input fields, where attackers input malicious scripts. When you click submit, the malicious script runs somewhere — could be your page, could be another page.",[12,361,362,363,366],{},"For example, your image's ",[51,364,365],{},"src"," attribute comes from user input, and the user input is a malicious script. When the page loads, the malicious script runs. Concept: user inputs:",[107,368,370],{"className":109,"code":369,"language":111,"meta":112,"style":112},"\u003Cscript>alert('Haha, you got XSS!');\u003C\u002Fscript>\n",[51,371,372],{"__ignoreMap":112},[116,373,374,376,379,382,386,389,392,395,397],{"class":118,"line":119},[116,375,147],{"class":129},[116,377,378],{"class":133},"script",[116,380,381],{"class":129},">",[116,383,385],{"class":384},"sj_SG","alert",[116,387,388],{"class":129},"(",[116,390,391],{"class":232},"'Haha, you got XSS!'",[116,393,394],{"class":129},");\u003C\u002F",[116,396,378],{"class":133},[116,398,141],{"class":129},[12,400,401],{},"Then the rendered result is:",[107,403,405],{"className":109,"code":404,"language":111,"meta":112,"style":112},"\u003Cimg src=\"#\" onerror=\"alert('Haha, you got XSS!');\">\n",[51,406,407],{"__ignoreMap":112},[116,408,409,411,413,416,418,421,424,426,429,431,434],{"class":118,"line":119},[116,410,147],{"class":129},[116,412,15],{"class":133},[116,414,415],{"class":137}," src",[116,417,229],{"class":129},[116,419,420],{"class":232},"\"#\"",[116,422,423],{"class":137}," onerror",[116,425,229],{"class":129},[116,427,428],{"class":232},"\"",[116,430,385],{"class":384},[116,432,433],{"class":232},"('Haha, you got XSS!');\"",[116,435,141],{"class":129},[56,437,439],{"id":438},"other-helmet-features","Other Helmet features",[12,441,442],{},"There's more — Helmet also has:",[335,444,445,448,451,454,457,460,463,466,469,472,474,477,479],{},[338,446,447],{},"Content-Security-Policy",[338,449,450],{},"Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy",[338,452,453],{},"Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy",[338,455,456],{},"Origin-Agent-Cluster",[338,458,459],{},"Referrer-Policy",[338,461,462],{},"Strict-Transport-Security",[338,464,465],{},"X-Content-Type-Options",[338,467,468],{},"X-DNS-Prefetch-Control",[338,470,471],{},"X-Download-Options",[338,473,101],{},[338,475,476],{},"X-Permitted-Cross-Domain-Policies",[338,478,87],{},[338,480,481],{},"X-XSS-Protection",[12,483,484,485,323],{},"These all help your app avoid known web attacks. They can be configured. For more, see ",[317,486,489],{"href":487,"rel":488},"https:\u002F\u002Fhelmetjs.github.io\u002F",[321],"the official docs",[20,491,493],{"id":492},"how-to-use-helmet-in-express","How to use Helmet in Express?",[12,495,496],{},"Using Helmet is super simple. Just install the Helmet package:",[107,498,502],{"className":499,"code":500,"language":501,"meta":112,"style":112},"language-bash shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","npm install helmet\n","bash",[51,503,504],{"__ignoreMap":112},[116,505,506,510,513],{"class":118,"line":119},[116,507,509],{"class":508},"s_sBn","npm",[116,511,512],{"class":232}," install",[116,514,515],{"class":232}," helmet\n",[12,517,518],{},"Then use Helmet in your code:",[107,520,524],{"className":521,"code":522,"language":523,"meta":112,"style":112},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","const express = require('express');\nconst helmet = require('helmet');\n\nconst app = express();\n\n\u002F\u002F ...other code omitted\n\napp.use(helmet());\n\n\u002F\u002F ...other code omitted\n\napp.listen(3000);\n","js",[51,525,526,549,567,573,587,591,596,600,616,620,624,628],{"__ignoreMap":112},[116,527,528,532,535,538,541,543,546],{"class":118,"line":119},[116,529,531],{"class":530},"sWyjQ","const",[116,533,534],{"class":137}," express",[116,536,537],{"class":530}," =",[116,539,540],{"class":384}," require",[116,542,388],{"class":129},[116,544,545],{"class":232},"'express'",[116,547,548],{"class":129},");\n",[116,550,551,553,556,558,560,562,565],{"class":118,"line":126},[116,552,531],{"class":530},[116,554,555],{"class":137}," helmet",[116,557,537],{"class":530},[116,559,540],{"class":384},[116,561,388],{"class":129},[116,563,564],{"class":232},"'helmet'",[116,566,548],{"class":129},[116,568,569],{"class":118,"line":144},[116,570,572],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":571},true,"\n",[116,574,575,577,580,582,584],{"class":118,"line":154},[116,576,531],{"class":530},[116,578,579],{"class":137}," app",[116,581,537],{"class":530},[116,583,534],{"class":384},[116,585,586],{"class":129},"();\n",[116,588,589],{"class":118,"line":164},[116,590,572],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":571},[116,592,593],{"class":118,"line":180},[116,594,595],{"class":122},"\u002F\u002F ...other code omitted\n",[116,597,598],{"class":118,"line":190},[116,599,572],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":571},[116,601,602,605,608,610,613],{"class":118,"line":200},[116,603,604],{"class":129},"app.",[116,606,607],{"class":384},"use",[116,609,388],{"class":129},[116,611,612],{"class":384},"helmet",[116,614,615],{"class":129},"());\n",[116,617,618],{"class":118,"line":215},[116,619,572],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":571},[116,621,622],{"class":118,"line":223},[116,623,595],{"class":122},[116,625,626],{"class":118,"line":236},[116,627,572],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":571},[116,629,630,632,635,637,640],{"class":118,"line":247},[116,631,604],{"class":129},[116,633,634],{"class":384},"listen",[116,636,388],{"class":129},[116,638,639],{"class":137},"3000",[116,641,548],{"class":129},[12,643,644,645,323],{},"Usage is the same as other middleware — just add it to ",[51,646,647],{},"app.use()",[68,649,650],{},[12,651,652,654,655,660],{},[73,653,75],{},"\nIf building Express from scratch is annoying, the official team also released ",[317,656,659],{"href":657,"rel":658},"https:\u002F\u002Fexpressjs.com\u002Fen\u002Fstarter\u002Fgenerator.html",[321],"Express Generator"," to quickly create an Express project.",[12,662,663,664,666],{},"By default, Helmet adds the things we mentioned above. If you want to customize, you can. For example, to set ",[51,665,101],{},":",[107,668,670],{"className":521,"code":669,"language":523,"meta":112,"style":112},"const express = require('express');\nconst helmet = require('helmet');\n\nconst app = expre